This paper discusses techniques for selecting the connections between layers of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the CIFAR and SVHN datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision research (cs.CV). The techniques discussed in the paper are relevant to both supervised and unsupervised learning (cs.LG), and involve optimizing the connections between layers to improve accuracy (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the co-occurrences of features, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves testing different methods for optimizing connections, which is a common topic in neural engineering (cs.NE).
